      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACKS ULTIMATE FURY NZ (7) overcame a second row draw for a 3m win as a hot favourite at Wagga last week and has won four of five second up attempts so should be improved. Draws wide but has a great strike rate at this distance and showed his class by placing in last year's Rising Sun. METEOR MOTH (10) scored back-to-back wins at this venue back in March and looks close to another success after seconds in his last appearances here, beaten only 1.2m last week. Looks suited up in distance having won four of his seven attempts. SWEET IDEAL (3) broke when resuming but draws much better and has won two of three second-up attempts so looks for big improvement. SOAP AND BUBBLES (1) has come from wider or second row draws to put together a series of top-four results. Should get her chance from the ace draw. JUSTALITTLESIP NZ (9) hasn't been far away of late and could threaten with some luck from the back row.",
